messages.content: Venor's mindscape is black and white, a small beach by a gigantic lake surrounded by woods. The only splash of colour is the lilac water.
"So." Venor is sitting by the shore as she brings Lamia here. "This is my place." The white walls surrounding the mindscape are new, but she doesn't comment on them.
"hm."
"Is that a bad hm or a good hm?" Venor crosses her legs.
"Just...don't know what to say."
"I.. See. Is it because of the colour thing?"
"kinda."
"It's a little jarring at first. I got used to it." She glances out at the lake. "...Don't go in there. Or drink from it. There's a fuckton of bodies in that thing."
Lamia dives in head first
(DBDJEBRJDBJWRB
//fdsafasdf
((OH MY GOD))

Venor smacks her forehead. "That is also all-encompassing fear!" She yells at Lamia but yeah it's too late. There are three bodies that float past Lamia. One is a wild-eyed girl with hair covering one dead, twisted eye. She has cat ears. Another is a lilac haired woman with twisted legs. Finally, a businessman that looks an awful lot like Venor's human form.
Lamia pops his head out of the water, a fish in his mouth
"How are you not drowning right now." Venor stares.
"Well in the mindscape I manifested this fish."
A corpse appears behind him
The corpse of a ||dog||
And then a moustached man
Some dude with a flat top
A buff one with blue hair
"Huh."
"What is something behind m-"
The dog starts attacking him
Venor outstretches a hand. "They can't come out of the lake. I can't go in without being paralyzed with fear."
Lamia throws the dog, but the flat top corpse is leaping at him
Venor sighs, takes a deep breath, and dives in. She can swim perfectly well, but now her limbs are all shaky. She drags Lamia towards the shore.
Lamia tossed her out. "DONT COME IN HERE!" more corpses appear. A tiny round senator. A corpse that looks an awful lot like Malachite
A corpse with two faces
And the biggest corpse of all
One that resembled a drunken man with a beard
The last one frightened lamia the most
Venor curses and sweeps the lake away with a glare. It.... evaporates. "Get out!" She yells. "I can't keep it like this forever."
Lamia gets out and starts hyperventilating
"Jesus. I told you not to dive into that." Venor releases the lake.
//I tried to remember everyone Dio had killed
//the ones that came to the top of my head were Dario, Danny, George, Dire, Jonathan, Nukesaku, Senator Wilson Philips and Kakyoin, but there's obviously more than that
((Those are the main ones I think ye))
//there were some cops in part 1, that random cat in part 3 for no reason, the people who got him out of his coffin, etc.
"What the fuck..."

"The lake is the embodiment of my fear. Aka the only emotion I have left to cling onto. Recently, though..." Venor raises a hand and a warm gold spreads briefly through the sand. "I think that's joy."
The gold fades away and Venor drops her hand, as if exhausted. "Rejoining society was a good idea."
Lamia
Genuinely smiles
A non bastard smile
Venor smiles back at him, and its her true smile as well. Gold begins to flood the sand again, and she's not even trying.
Lamia sees the sand
"...imma build a sand castle."
"Cool."
Lamia fucking manifests a sand castle
"H...How. Why. What." Venor looks at Lamia weirdly. "I have so many questions."
"In the mindscape, you can manifest anything."

"I didn't know in each *other's* minds, though... And I've never been able to do that. Just manipulate it a little bit." Venor looks away. "You're the first person apart from me and the bodies that's been here, y'know."
"I have a strong willpower." Suddenly a Utahraptor manifests
(DIEGO?
It has "DIO" all over it
(DIEGO!!!!!
"Why is there a dinosaur in my mindscape." Venor asks flatly.
((dfghdlkgjhdfgjk DIEGO))
"One time I imagined what I would look like as a dinosaur. Now it's my favorite mental creation."
"Looks cool, to be honest." Venor tilts her head at it.
The dinosaur uses it's head to lift Venor onto it's back and lets out a chirp
Venor laughs. The sand sparkles a little bit. "I'm riding a *dinosaur*. That was my childhood dream!" Her laugh is genuine, for once.
"Well let Diosaurus, as I call him, make your dreams come true!"
"Diosaurus." Venor claps her hands in delight. "I love it."
"I'm a genius, I know."
Venor laughs at him. The gold colour is here to stay- The water is a little clearer, and the sand sparkles beautifully.
The dinosaur runs at a moderate speed
Venor has, funnily enough, never ridden a dinosaur. It's different from horses, certainly, and she laughs as the Diosaurus runs.
"Now what else could I manifest..."
fuckin
bouncy castle
"Fuck yeah."
"What is that."
"A bouncy castle. I've only ever heard of these things."
"Huh. Never heard of one myself."
Lamia takes off his shoes.
and gets in
Venor follows. "Uh. What do you do in this?"
"Supposedly you just fuckin bounce around."
"Okay..." Venor jumps and shoots straight into the stratosphere. She has the capabilities of jumping incredibly high and now with bounce...
(THIS IS MAKING ME ALUGH
Lamia tests out the bouncy castle in a very Dio way
soon he's laughing like an idiot
Venor rejoins him after about 30 seconds and shoots straight up again. "Fuck gravityyyyyyyyyy-" She yells as she shoots away again.
"If only I had a gravity manipulation stand...speaking of gravity did you notice things got weird earlier?"
Venor finally touches down. "A little. It was really strange."
"I have a feeling I know what happened."
"Oh?"
"Remember when I told you about Pucci earlier?"
"Yeah?" Venor waves her tail.
"It's C Moon."
"Ah. Gotcha. What was he using that for?"
"I don't know. I don't know how he got it even! Is there a green baby?"
"A... A green baby..."
"Re-explain the green baby again."
"So there's a green baby that comes from Jonathan's bone. I don't fucking remember why."
"You say these 14 meaningless words to it and it's power merges with yours."
"...Right."
"HOW DID IT SHOW UP IN THE VOID?!"
"I don't know???" Venor looks concerned.
"THAT'S WHAT I'M WONDERING!"
Venor frowns. "That is... weird."
"It is..."
"I would say we should go search for clues but. Blind." Venor shrugs.
"Well I know a thing or 2 about how people like to solve mysteries."
"Yeah? I didn't know you were a detective." Venor teases.
"Well I've seen some...detective shows that humans like to watch."
//by that he means Scooby Doo
((Thought as much))
"I watched like one. It gave me PTSD." Venor spent most of her human adventure running from a crazed detective.
"We're going to need a crew, a van and a talking dog."
//adfadsfadfasf
"Right. Let's do this." Venor doesn't question it.
"And a groovy theme song."
"Hmm... I can sing, and I play the guitar fairly well... And I can keyboard a little."
"I know there have been blind musicians before."
"Oh, yeah I guess so."
"Or we could just investigate ourselves."
"Oh. Yeah that's also a thing."
"Tell me do humans usually solve mysteries with talking mutts?"
"I don't know. Roxy didn't have a mutt but her stand, Fun Ghoul, was like a cat."
"I'll be honest, Scooby-Doo might not be the best depiction of real world detectives."
"Maybe. I mean. Roxy had a team. And a van. We had a van as well... maybe I was the detective all along! We had a talking gecko as well...."
"Your adventures seem interesting."
"They were certainly... odd. Bizarre, even."
((Badum tsh))
Lamia groans for some reason
Venor cackles. "I have no idea what it is about that word. Bizarre."
"It just....urks me."
"Fair enough. Maybe I can get into Morise's files one day and find out why."
"Should we wake up now or..?"
"Ah. Yeah." Venor takes a lasting look at the colours. "I'm going to miss being able to see."
Lamia frowned
"I mean temporarily but still."
Lamia nods
"...Right then." Venor sounds mildly frightened as she takes a deep breath.
Lamia wakes up too
Another color flows through her mindscape - red.
Venor rocks to herself on the sandy beach, tears adding to her lake of purple. *He didn't mean it... You read his emotion. He didn't mean it.*
//would lamia be here too
((I guess so))
//idk what to fucking do oops
//imsoryr
She drops in, does a superhero landing, and screws up her eyes. It's so *bright* in here, what the hell? She takes some time to go lounge on the beach.
dinosaur is still here
"...Well. Not the weirdest thing." She heads over and pats the dinosaur.
it purrs
"Lamia, your dinosaur is a cat now." She murmurs, and laughs.
The dinosaur chirps
She grins at it.
it licks her hand
"Why." She sighs.
it grins at her
"Oh, of *course* Lamia's dinosaur is like that." She giggles. "...I really do miss him."
The dinosaur opened it's mouth
and played what seemed to be a recording of Lamia's voice

"I have the perfect plan for testing new recruits for a rescue mission. You 4 will take control of the cheap animatronics in this restaurant and be all spooky and shit. At some point you'll have to come after the night guard and pose an actual threat, but please, for the love of whatever God you pray to, don't kill them!"
"Lamia what the fuck." She sits bolt upright. "Dinosaur, you got any contact with Lamia??"
the dinosaur shook it's head
"Ah. I'll have to get a message through Polaris or something. If he gets himself hurt or killed trying to rescue my dumb ass I'm gonna kill him." She grits her teeth.
"I can use my position as manager of this shitshow to recruit an army!"
She buries her face in the sand. "I give up on that bitch."
The dinosaur wrote *here's what's happening now* in the sand followed by the sounds of a malfunctioning robot
"That's... I'm very confused. This sucks. I'm gonna tell Ombrage or *something* to stop him." She mutters.
The dinosaur simply makes a dinosaur sound
"Hm." She lies back down on the sand and looks up at the sky.
